    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Bálint Sárközy (Vienna, 9 December 1540)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>Oláh is certain that Bálint Sárközy remembers what Oláh told him in
                            Bratislava, i.e. that if a citizen of a mining town needs help at the
                            court of law, Sárközy should support them. He thus now asks him to help
                            the citizens of the mining town, who will not be ungrateful. The Queen
                            does not currently have any lawsuits pending. Oláh will travel to the
                            Queen together with the King, and he will talk to her about Sárközy;
                            Oláh will recount in person or via mail what the Queen answers. He will
                            share the details of the Bratislava affair with magister canonicus Máté
                            Bősi before he leaves from here.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Salutem plurimam, Egregie Domine et Amice Honorande!<note type="critic"
                        >Bálint Sárközy of Foktő.</note></p>
                <p>Memoria tenere Dominationem Vestram puto me <placeName>Posonii</placeName> ei
                    locutum fuisse, ut si cives civitatum montanarum aut alium quempiam subditum
                    maiestatis reginalis aliquid causarum habere in iudiciis contingeret, vellet eos
                    habere commendatos patrociniumque ac defensionem eorum suscipere. Quemadmodum
                    igitur prius ita nunc quoque Dominationem Vestram rogo, velit montanarum
                    civitatum cives habere commendatos. Et si quam prosequi causam habuerit, eamque
                    requisiverit ipsorum curam suscipere, qui non erunt Dominationi Vestrae ingrati.
                    Quod autem ad solius maiestatis reginalis causas agendas ac defendendas attinet,
                    nunc maiestas sua nihil habet, quod sciam, litium. Proficiscar cum maiestate
                    regia ad maiestatem <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">suam</add> reginalem,
                    cum qua de persona Dominationis Vestrae loquar, ut si quid habitura esset,
                    maiestas sua in Hungaria causarum in eo opera Dominationis Vestrae utatur.
                    Quicquid autem sua maiestas responderit, vel solus ipse referam Dominationi
                    Vestrae, cum Deo dante revertar, vel per litteras quamprimum significabo. </p>
                <p>In negotio meo Posoniensi scribam ad Dominationem Vestram ante quam hinc sim
                    discessurus, et relinquam informationem apud dominum <persName>magistrum
                        Matheum</persName><note type="critic">Máté Bősi was Canon of Bratislava
                        between 1520 and 1549.</note> decimatorem et canonicum Posoniensem.
                    Dominatio Vestra feliciter valeat.</p>
                <p><placeName>Viennae</placeName> 9. Decembris 1540.</p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="signature">Vester Nicolaus Olahus custos Albensis consiliarius regiae
                        maiestatis etc. sua manu</seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Egregio domino Valentino litterato de Fokthew etc. domino et amico honorando.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
